      "content": "thanks. but it feels like the \"against\" side always focuses on things that could happen but haven't, whereas the \"for\" side is based on the actual carbon numbers. is it really a fair debate if one side is basically just saying \"what if\" while the other is looking at the math for hitting net zero?",
